Replicates

Author

Kantnerova et al. (2023)

Published

November 3, 2023

Setup

Using R version 4.3.1 (2023-06-16) , tidyverse version 2.0.0, and isoorbi version 1.2.9.

# load packages
library(isoorbi) # for orbitrap function
library(dplyr) # for mutating data frames
library(stringr) # for extarcting text information
library(forcats) # for recoding factors
library(ggplot2) # for data visualization
library(cowplot) # arrange multipanel plots

Data

# isotopocules data
data <- 
  "data/replicates" |>
  orbi_find_isox() |>
  orbi_read_isox() |>
  orbi_flag_satellite_peaks() |> 
  orbi_flag_weak_isotopocules(min_percent = 30) |> 
  # very tight agc data, discard anything that's 5% above or below the mean
  orbi_flag_outliers(agc_fold_cutoff = 1.05) |>
  # pull out replicate from filename
  mutate(
    replicate = str_extract(filename, "Replicate_\\d") |> str_replace("_", " ")
  ) |>
  # expand amino acid names
  mutate(
    compound = compound |>
      fct_recode(
        "Alanine" = "Ala_imm",
        "Arginine" = "Arg_imm",
        "Methionine" = "Met_imm",
        "Phenylalanine" = "Phe_imm"
      )
  )
#> orbi_read_isox() is loading .isox data from 5 file(s)...
#> - loaded 6153 peaks for 4 compounds (Ala_imm, Arg_imm, Met_imm, Phe_imm) with
#>    6 isotopocules (M0, 15N, 13C, 2H, 33S, 34S) from
#>    MRFA_MS2_120kRes_1E6AGC_50NCE_10min_10uscans_Replicate_1.isox in 0.30
#>    seconds.
#> - loaded 6138 peaks for 4 compounds (Ala_imm, Arg_imm, Met_imm, Phe_imm) with
#>    6 isotopocules (M0, 15N, 13C, 2H, 33S, 34S) from
#>    MRFA_MS2_120kRes_1E6AGC_50NCE_10min_10uscans_Replicate_2.isox in 0.05
#>    seconds.
#> - loaded 6143 peaks for 4 compounds (Ala_imm, Arg_imm, Met_imm, Phe_imm) with
#>    6 isotopocules (M0, 15N, 13C, 2H, 33S, 34S) from
#>    MRFA_MS2_120kRes_1E6AGC_50NCE_10min_10uscans_Replicate_3.isox in 0.04
#>    seconds.
#> - loaded 6120 peaks for 4 compounds (Ala_imm, Arg_imm, Met_imm, Phe_imm) with
#>    6 isotopocules (M0, 15N, 13C, 2H, 33S, 34S) from
#>    MRFA_MS2_120kRes_1E6AGC_50NCE_10min_10uscans_Replicate_4.isox in 0.05
#>    seconds.
#> - loaded 6167 peaks for 4 compounds (Ala_imm, Arg_imm, Met_imm, Phe_imm) with
#>    6 isotopocules (M0, 15N, 13C, 2H, 33S, 34S) from
#>    MRFA_MS2_120kRes_1E6AGC_50NCE_10min_10uscans_Replicate_5.isox in 0.05
#>    seconds.
#> orbi_flag_satellite_peaks() is flagging minor signals (satellite peaks)...
#>    ...flagged 10051/30721 peaks in 6 isotopocules ("M0", "15N", "13C", "2H",
#>    "33S", "34S") as satellite peaks (32.7%) in 0.97 seconds.
#> orbi_flag_weak_isotopocules() is flagging isotopocules from data that are
#>    detected in less than 30% of scans in 5 data group(s) (based on
#>    'filename')...
#>    ...confirmed there are no weak isotopocules in 0.05 seconds.
#> orbi_flag_outliers() is flagging the scans below 1/1.05 and above 1.05 times
#>    the average number of ions (`tic` * `it.ms`) in the Orbitrap analyzer in 5
#>    data group(s) (based on 'filename')...
#>    ...flagged 4/1151 scans (0.3%) as outliers (use `orbi_plot_raw_data(y =
#>    tic * it.ms)` to visualize them) across all data groups in 0.07 seconds.

# calculate ratios for 13C/M0
ratios <- data |>
  orbi_define_basepeak("M0") |>
  orbi_filter_isox(isotopocules = "13C") |>
  group_by(replicate) |>
  orbi_summarize_results(ratio_method = "sum") 
#> orbi_define_basepeak() is setting the 'M0' isotopocule as the ratio
#>    denominator...
#>    ...set base peak and calculated 18031 ratios for 5 isotopocules/base peak
#>    (15N, 13C, 2H, 33S, 34S) in 0.29 seconds.
#> orbi_filter_isox() is filtering the dataset by isotopocules (13C)...
#>    ...removed 12003/18031 rows (66.6%) in 0.00 seconds.
#> orbi_summarize_results() is grouping the data by 'replicate', 'filename',
#>    'compound', 'basepeak', 'isotopocule' and summarizing ratios from 4588
#>    peaks (excluded 1440 flagged peaks; excluded 0 unused peaks) using the
#>    'sum' method...
#>    ...completed in 0.04 seconds.

Figure 11 top panel

p_top <- data |>
  orbi_plot_raw_data(
    isotopocules = "M0",
    x_breaks = c(5, 10),
    y = intensity,
    y_scale = "log",
    color = compound,
    show_outliers = FALSE
  ) +
  facet_wrap(~replicate, nrow = 1) +
  labs(x = "time / min", y = "EIC / arb. unit") +
  theme(strip.text = element_text(size = 16))
p_top

Figure 11 bottom panel

p_bottom <- 
  ratios |>
  ggplot() +
  aes(
    replicate, ratio, color = compound, shape = compound,
    ymin = ratio - ratio_sem, ymax = ratio + ratio_sem
  ) +
  # standard deviations
  geom_rect(
    data = function(df) 
      df |> group_by(compound) |>
      summarize(ratio_mean = mean(ratio), ratio_sd = sd(ratio)),
    map = aes(
      ymin = ratio_mean - ratio_sd, ymax = ratio_mean + ratio_sd,
      x = NULL, y = NULL, xmin = -Inf, xmax = +Inf, color = NULL),
    fill = "gray90", show.legend = FALSE
  ) +
  # averages
  geom_hline(
    data = function(df) 
      df |> group_by(compound) |>
      summarize(ratio_mean = mean(ratio)),
    map = aes(yintercept = ratio_mean, color = compound),
    show.legend = FALSE
  ) +
  # data points
  geom_errorbar(width = 0.1, show.legend = FALSE) + 
  geom_point(fill = "white", size = 3) +
  facet_grid(compound ~ ., scales = "free_y") +
  # scales
  scale_color_brewer(palette = "Dark2") +
  scale_shape_manual(values = c(21:25)) +
  scale_y_continuous(breaks = scales::pretty_breaks(3)) +
  # labels
  labs(x = NULL, color = NULL, shape = NULL,
       y = expression("ratio ("^13*C/M0*")")) +
  # theme
  theme_bw() +
  theme(
    text = element_text(size = 16),
    panel.grid = element_blank(),
    strip.background = element_blank(),
    strip.text = element_blank(),
    axis.ticks.x = element_blank(),
    legend.position = "top"
  )
p_bottom

Figure 11 combined

plot_grid(
  p_top + theme(legend.position = "none"), p_bottom,
  ncol = 1, rel_heights = c(1, 2), align = "v", axis = "lr"
)

# Setup

Using `r R.version.string` , tidyverse version `r packageVersion("tidyverse")`, and isoorbi version `r packageVersion("isoorbi")`.

```{r}
#| label: setup
#| message: false

# load packages
library(isoorbi) # for orbitrap function
library(dplyr) # for mutating data frames
library(stringr) # for extarcting text information
library(forcats) # for recoding factors

library(cowplot) # arrange multipanel plots
```
